Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses the denotational semantics for a region-based effect system, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.TL (Type Theory and Logic). Additionally, the paper addresses the problem of spurious functional dependencies, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the concept of "fictional purity," which is related to the sub-category of cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
